<HEAD>Thunderstorms Spawn Tornadoes in Ohio Valley</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms lingered over parts of Tennessee, Kentucky, Ohio
and Indiana early today, hours after severe thunderstorms produced
15 tornadoes in the Ohio Valley.
   Severe thunderstorms spawned six tornadoes in Illinois, five
tornadoes in Indiana and four in Kentucky during the late afternoon
and evening Friday.
   Funnel clouds were reported and tornadoes touched down in
central Illinois near Champaign, while winds and rain left 1,200
people in the Belleville area without power for more than four
hours.
   Rain across the state ranged from 1.2 inches in the northeast to
half an inch in extreme southern Illinois.
   In Indiana, tornadoes downed power lines and overturned at least
one trailer, but there were no immediate reports of injuries Friday.
   Two barns were blown down by a tornado at Philpot, Ky., and
another two barns were destroyed by a twister at Whitesville, Ky.
Elsewhere in the state, Hardinsburg received 2{ inches of rain in
less than an hour.
   Strong thunderstorms were developing along a cold front crossing
Oklahoma early this morning.
   Showers and a few thunderstorms also fell over the central Gulf
Coast and over eastern Minnesota and west-central Wisconsin.
   Dry weather prevailed across the rest of the nation, with clear
skies over much of the West.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms from the
Great Lakes across the Ohio and Tennessee valleys to the eastern
half of the Gulf Coast; scattered showers and thunderstorms over
the southern Plains and along the eastern slopes of the central and
southern Rockies; and strong winds from the northern Rockies to the
upper Mississippi Valley.
   Predicted highs: 60s from the Pacific Northwest across the
northern Rockies and the northern Plains to upper Michigan; 90s in
Florida, Louisiana and parts of Texas and Southern California; 100s
in the Rio Grande Valley of Texas and across the desert Southwest;
and 70s and 80s across much of the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures across the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 27
degrees at Yellowstone Park in Wyoming to 82 at Phoenix and Corpus
Christi and Del Rio in Texas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 68 cloudy; Boston 57 fair; Charleston, S.C. 63
fair; Cincinnati 63 cloudy; Cleveland 67 cloudy; Detroit 64 rain;
Miami 74 fair; New York 56 fair; Philadelphia 58 partly cloudy;
Pittsburgh 65 partly cloudy; Portland, Maine 50 foggy; Washington
62 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 48 fair; Chicago 61 foggy; Dallas-Fort Worth
78 fair; Denver 56 fair; Des Moines 58 fair; Indianapolis 59 foggy;
Kansas City 63 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 55 partly cloudy;
Nashville 74 thunderstorms; New Orleans 78 foggy; St. Louis 66 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 62 fair; Anchorage 47 fair; Las Vegas 72
fair; Los Angeles 59 fair; Phoenix 82 fair; Salt Lake City 45 fair;
San Diego 62 fair; San Francisco 51 fair; Seattle 50 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 63 cloudy; Toronto 59 hazy.
