<SECOND>AM-BRF--Time Stops,0115</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Steamroller Crushes 6,000 Fake Watches</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police used a steamroller Saturday to
crush about 6,000 watches with famous but phony brand names, part
of a crackdown on Bangkok's booming market in fake luxury items.
   Crushed on the street in front of a riverside police station
were watches carrying brand names such as Cartier, Rolex, Gucci,
Omega, Longines and Seiko.
   The watches are openly sold at numerous street stalls in the
Thai capital. A fake Rolex sells for about $35, compared with more
than $1,000 for some authentic models.
   The United States in particular has complained about Thailand's
wholesale piracy of foreign goods, patents, copyrights and
trademarks.
</TEXT>
