<TEXT>
   Two fishermen who planned to catch
fish by tossing explosives into the sea were killed when a stick of
dynamite went off too soon, the coast guard said Saturday.
   Chief Petty Officer Crisanto Sy said the men were killed Friday
just off the island of Rapu-Rapu, about 230 miles southeast of
Manila. He said a stick of dynamite blew up as soon as one of the
