<HEAD>Bus Crash Kills 14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A speeding bus rolled off a road,
hit a rock and exploded in flames Saturday, killing at least 14
people and injuring 10, the national news agency Tanjug said.
   The 3:45 a.m. accident occurred between Ivangrad and Sarajevo in
central Yugoslavia, the report said. The vehicle disintegrated and
authorities still were trying to determine the exact number of
dead, the report said.
   A 70-foot section of railing pierced the bus like a lance as the
vehicle left the road, Tanjug said.
   Tanjug quoted a Sarajevo doctor as saying two people were in
critical condition with burns over 75 percent of their bodies.
