<HEAD>One Killed, 16 Injured in Czechoslovakia Train Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One passenger was killed and 16
others were injured when an express train jumped off the tracks,
the Communist Party daily Rude Pravo said Saturday.
   The likely cause of the accident was the ``changed shape of the
rail due to excessive heat,'' the daily said.
   Czechoslovakia has been experiencing unusually hot weather for
this time of year, with temperatures during the day hovering around
86 degrees.
   Six cars were derailed in the accident, which occurred between
the cities of Kolin and Kutna Hora, 43 miles east of Prague.
