<HEAD>Interior Minister Warns of Attacks Following Hamadi Sentencing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interior Minister Wolfgang Schaeuble
warned of an increased risk of terrorist attacks following the life
sentence imposed on TWA hijacker Mohammed Ali Hamadi, a newspaper
reported Saturday.
   ``The risk of terrorist attacks and hijackings has increased
considerably,'' the Hamburg-based Bild am Sonntag newspaper quoted
Schaeuble as saying.
   Schaeuble said security had been stepped up at the nation's
