<SECOND>PM-Digest Briefs,0695</SECOND>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government says the U.S. Embassy
was indirectly involved in post-election violence this month that
left three opposition leaders injured and one of their bodyguards
dead.
   U.S. Embassy spokesman Terry Kneebone, responding to a
government communique issued late Friday, said the attempted
linkage was ``propaganda foolishness.''
   Police on Friday arrested 17 Panamanians who provide security at
U.S. Embassy offices, the embassy reported. Fifteen were quickly
